record_data.record_plain_text:
TransCanada Energy Sales Ltd. RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
1. Availability: TransCanada Energy Sales Ltd. ("TES") makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom TES has contracted.
2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy and/or capacity by TES not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of TES.
3. Rates: All sales pursuant to this Rate Schedule shall be made at rates negotiated between the purchaser and TES.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions for purchases of electric energy and capacity shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and TES.
5. Compliance with Commission Regulations: TES shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning TES's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes TES to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits TES's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning TES's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Rate Schedule.
6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: TES has requested and been granted the following waivers and exemptions in connection with its market-based rate authority, pursuant to Commission order approving this Rate Schedule under Docket No. ER09-328-001: (i) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (ii) waiver of Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141 of the Commission's regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements and (iii) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act, 16 U.S.C. Section; 824c, and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities and assumptions of liability.
7. Ancillary Services.
a. RTO/ISO Specific.
i. PJM: TES offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. ii. New York: TES offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
iii. New England: TES offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
iv. California: TES offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO.
8. Seller Category: TES is a Category 1 Seller, as defined in 18 C.F.R. Section; 35.36(a), in all Regions.
